### Google Cloud Platform - 6.5 Class Notes - Taught by Theo WAF aka Mookie aka Suge WAF @ CloudRow Records - April 22, 2025

##Step by Step Notes & Diagrams

1. Open Gitbash on your Windows desktop, or Terminal on your Macintosh desktop (DON'T USE POWERSHELL!!!)
2. Type in PWD (Present Working Directory) KNOW WHERE YOU ARE!
3. LS = Lists folders
4. DON'T STORE YOUR FILES/CODE/OR WORK IN ONEDRIVE (You'll be sorry...)
5. In GitBash, navigate to this folder to store your repo -> cd Users/Documents/TheoWAF/class6.5/
6. Command To Know: pwd: Print the current working directory, ls: List directory contents, cd: Change directory, mkdir: Create a new directory, rmdir: Remove an empty directory, touch: Create a new empty file, cp: Copy files or directories, mv: Move or rename files or directories, rm: Delete files or directories, cat: View file contents, nano: Open file in Nano text editor, chmod: Change file permissions, chown: Change file owner or group, echo: Display a message or variable, clear: Clear the terminal screen
7. Create a new folder with the 'mkdir' command, call it whatever you want
8. mkdir gcp if you don't have gcp folder
9. go to your github, click on repositories
10. create a new repo, name it whatever, click on Create Repo
11. On the next page that says "Quick setup - if you've done this kind of thing before", create a new tab and NEVER click off this page!!!
12. Click on copy ...create a new repository on the command line, screenshot it, whatever...copy that to your notepad
13. Go back to your Gitbash
14. git clone your repo from Github
15. Add a file to your repo from gitbash -> echo "# sample1" >> README.md
16. Add another file and add text to the file by doing this by checking the end of the echo command -> echo "i dont know" >> idontknow.txt
17. Use the command 'cat' to see inside your txt file -> cat idontknow.txt
18. In Gitbash, run 'git init'
19. git status
20. git add .
21. git status
22. git commit -m "add a comment here"
23. git branch -M main
24. git remote add origin "your git repo link here"
25. git push -u origin main
